{"id": "duc04-testb-31:9#27", "contents": "Premier-designate Bulent Ecevit is facing a challenging task in convincing ex-premier Tansu Ciller's center-right party to join forces in a secular coalition. Ecevit, who was asked to form a new government on Wednesday, requires the support of Ciller's 99 deputies to move forward. The backing of another center-right party, led by Mesut Yilmaz, has already been secured, but Yilmaz's long-standing rivalry with Ciller complicates Ecevit's efforts to build a coalition."}
